<exercise checkit-seed="0002" checkit-slug="CC3" checkit-title="Constant-Coefficient Linear Homogeneous Higher-Order ODEs">
  <statement>
    <p>Explain how to find the general solution to each given ODE using
        exponential functions.</p>
    <p>For each exponential solution using complex numbers, also provide
        an alternate general solution using only real numbers.</p>
      <ol>
        <li>
            <me>87 \, {y} = -3 \, {y''} + 30 \, {y'}</me>
        </li>
        <li>
            <me>-2 \, {y} - 4 \, {y'} = 2 \, {y''}</me>
        </li>
        <li>
            <me>18 \, {y''} = 15 \, {y'} + 3 \, {y'''}</me>
        </li>
      </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <ol>
        <li><me>
            {y} = c_{1} e^{\left(2 \, i t + 5 \, t\right)} + c_{2} e^{\left(-2 \, i t + 5 \, t\right)};\qquad
            {y} = {\left(k_{1} \cos\left(2 \, t\right) + k_{2} \sin\left(2 \, t\right)\right)} e^{\left(5 \, t\right)}
         </me></li>
        <li><me>
            
            {y} = k_{1} t e^{\left(-t\right)} + k_{2} e^{\left(-t\right)}
         </me></li>
        <li><me>
            
            {y} = k_{2} e^{\left(5 \, t\right)} + k_{1} e^{t} + k_{3}
         </me></li>
      </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>
